    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "1. About Market, Opinion and Social Research"
      ],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "1.1 Market research is comprised of all forms of market, opinion, and social research (herein referred to as “Market Research”).",
      "char_len": 128,
      "chunk_word_count": 21,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.908256880733945,
        "digit": 0.01834862385321101,
        "non_space": 0.8515625
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5186926605504587,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "1. About Market, Opinion and Social Research"
      ],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "1.2 Market Research is the systematic gathering, analysis and interpretation of information about individuals or organisations. It uses the statistical and/or analytical methods and techniques of the applied social, behavioural, data and other sciences to generate insight and support decision making by providers of goods and services, governments, non-profit organisations and the general public.",
      "char_len": 398,
      "chunk_word_count": 56,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9652173913043478,
        "digit": 0.005797101449275362,
        "non_space": 0.8668341708542714
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9739130434782609,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "1. About Market, Opinion and Social Research"
      ],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "1.3 Market Research stands at the heart of well-informed commercial, social and political decisions. Its purpose is to deliver information and insights about people’s behaviour, needs and attitudes to inform decision making by providers of goods and services, governments, individuals, and society at large. Insight into what makes the success of a product, business initiative, consumer behaviour or government policy strategy is often the hidden – yet defining – factor that determines success and failure. It is our sector that provides the deeper intelligence needed for our world today by representing citizens’",
      "char_len": 616,
      "chunk_word_count": 92,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9657142857142857,
        "digit": 0.0038095238095238095,
        "non_space": 0.8522727272727273
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9742857142857144,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "1. About Market, Opinion and Social Research"
      ],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "authentic voices, from all levels of society, in an unbiased and representative way by applying the tenets of statistical and scientific methods.",
      "char_len": 145,
      "chunk_word_count": 22,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9758064516129032,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8551724137931035
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5846326164874552,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p13",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "1. About Market, Opinion and Social Research"
      ],
      "ordinal": 13,
      "text": "1.4 Market Research associations apply a comprehensive framework for self-regulation to ensure that researchers meet their ethical, professional, and legal responsibilities to the individuals whose data they use in research and to the clients and organisations which commission research. Members subscribe to self-regulation schemes that protect respondents' and participants' rights.",
      "char_len": 384,
      "chunk_word_count": 51,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9671641791044776,
        "digit": 0.005970149253731343,
        "non_space": 0.8723958333333334
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9753731343283583,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p14",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "2. Purpose of our Response"
      ],
      "ordinal": 14,
      "text": "2.1. Our associations are responding to the European Commission's call for evidence: Digital Fairness Act. Our associations welcome the European Commission's initiative, which aims to protect consumers from manipulative design practices—commonly referred to as \"dark patterns\"—and promote fairness in digital environments. Our response seeks to:",
      "char_len": 345,
      "chunk_word_count": 48,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9501661129568106,
        "digit": 0.006644518272425249,
        "non_space": 0.8724637681159421
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.962624584717608,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p15",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "2. Purpose of our Response"
      ],
      "ordinal": 15,
      "text": "Support the Act's objectives.",
      "char_len": 29,
      "chunk_word_count": 4,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9230769230769231,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.896551724137931
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.39230769230769236,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p16",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "2. Purpose of our Response"
      ],
      "ordinal": 16,
      "text": "Clarify the implications for the research and insights sector.",
      "char_len": 62,
      "chunk_word_count": 9,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9814814814814815,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8709677419354839
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.43611111111111117,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p17",
      "section_id": "s3",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "2. Purpose of our Response"
      ],
      "ordinal": 17,
      "text": "Ensure that legitimate research practices are not inadvertently restricted.",
      "char_len": 75,
      "chunk_word_count": 9,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9850746268656716,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8933333333333333
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.4388059701492537,
        "flags": [
          "very_short"
        ]
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p18",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 18,
      "text": "3.1. We strongly support the Act's aim to protect consumers, particularly vulnerable groups from manipulative digital practices. We recognise the importance of protecting social media users against so called \"dark patterns\", and in particular the concern raised for the potential impact on children and other vulnerable individuals. The inclusion of best practices for interface design and transparency is a welcome step.",
      "char_len": 421,
      "chunk_word_count": 62,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9667590027700831,
        "digit": 0.00554016620498615,
        "non_space": 0.8574821852731591
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9750692520775623,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p19",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 19,
      "text": "3.2. We recommend that the definitions of \"dark patterns\" in the Act be clearly contextualised to apply specifically to consumer-facing digital services. Techniques such as emotional nudging or visual cues, when used in behavioural science research, serve legitimate and ethical purposes.",
      "char_len": 288,
      "chunk_word_count": 42,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9556451612903226,
        "digit": 0.008064516129032258,
        "non_space": 0.8611111111111112
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.8750672043010753,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "Behavioural techniques, such as emotional nudging, stirring affects, and the use of visual cues are common tools in behavioural science research and are often employed for legitimate and ethical purposes. In these contexts, such techniques are used to study human decision-making, improve the effectiveness of public interest campaigns, or enhance policy interventions. For instance, researchers may use emotionally evocative messaging or visual prompts in a controlled and ethical manner to better understand how people respond to health warnings, safety communications, or social responsibility campaigns.",
      "char_len": 607,
      "chunk_word_count": 84,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9751908396946565,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8632619439868204
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9813931297709924,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "These methods, while similar in form to what may be described as \"dark patterns\" in manipulative digital interface design, are applied in a fundamentally different context. In behavioural research, there is typically informed consent, ethical oversight, and transparency, all of which distinguish these practices from the deceptive tactics that dark pattern regulations aim to curb. For example, 'stirring effects', which appeal to emotions",
      "char_len": 440,
      "chunk_word_count": 63,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9629629629629629,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8590909090909091
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9722222222222223,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "and include visual nudges to determine behaviour, can be a legitimate approach for the purposes of market, opinion and social research when undertaking behavioural science research.",
      "char_len": 181,
      "chunk_word_count": 26,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9807692307692307,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.861878453038674
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6494658119658119,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "Misapplication of the definition of “dark patterns” could inadvertently conflate unethical commercial manipulation with scientifically rigorous and ethically governed research methods. This conflation poses a serious risk: it could undermine valuable research methodologies and disrupt activities in sectors such as market, opinion, and social research, where behavioural science plays a vital role in understanding public sentiment, guiding public policy, and improving service delivery and decision-making. If market research techniques were improperly restricted under a broad interpretation of dark patterns, researchers and organisations could be disincentivised from employing them, thereby compromising the depth and quality of insight derived from these studies.",
      "char_len": 770,
      "chunk_word_count": 100,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9791356184798807,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8714285714285714
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9843517138599106,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "Finally, many of these research techniques are not aimed at inducing commercial transactions or manipulating user decisions for profit, which is the typical concern associated with dark patterns in consumer-facing digital services. Rather, their aim is often to benefit the public interest or to support evidence-based policy design.",
      "char_len": 333,
      "chunk_word_count": 48,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9755244755244755,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8588588588588588
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9816433566433567,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p25",
      "section_id": "s4",
      "section_path": [
        "EFAMRO and ESOMAR Consultation Response",
        "3. Our considerations"
      ],
      "ordinal": 25,
      "text": "We urge the European Commission to ensure that the definition of dark patterns is both context-specific and narrowly tailored. It should clearly differentiate between exploitative interface design in digital consumer platforms and the legitimate use of behavioural science methodologies in non-promotional or research contexts, which are undergirded by robust regulation, including ethical standards, Codes of Conduct and best practice, such as those developed by the ICC/ESOMAR International Code. Such clarity will help maintain the integrity and utility of behavioural research practices, while still enabling the Act to effectively target harmful manipulative practices in the digital consumer space.",
      "char_len": 704,
      "chunk_word_count": 98,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9819078947368421,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8636363636363636
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9864309210526316,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p26",
      "section_id": "s5",
